narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I started developing my own research to a greater degree in this semester than last semester. As a research seminar I think it was very effective. I learned from my peers as well, from watching them present their own research and field questions about their methods, inquiries, and so on.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I thought the organization (talking for a few minutes before some sessions to get everyone on the same page about who would present when) was well done.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. We had an undergraduate in this seminar and it was great to have that intersection between graduate and undergrad. This is such a good environment to pursue research and get feedback from peers I would like to pinpoint some formal aspects that I can later use in other environments to bring them up to a good speed.
